# Asterism production config.
# EASIEST: run `./scripts/init-secrets.sh <server-ip-or-domain>` — it generates
# asterism.env with strong random secrets (chmod 600) and prints the login
# password. The lines below are the manual alternative:
#   cp asterism.env.example asterism.env   # then edit
# `asterism.env` is gitignored and loaded via `env_file`. NOTE: modern Docker
# Compose INTERPOLATES env_file values, so a literal `$` is read as a variable
# reference. The secrets below are meant to be hex (no `$`) — if any value you set
# contains `$`, double it to `$$`. Do NOT commit asterism.env.

# ─── Domain / TLS (Caddy) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The host clients use — ALWAYS set it (no empty default). Use the server's public
# IP for a self-signed cert (browser warning; fine for a private box), or a FQDN
# for a real cert. (Caddy sets default_sni from this so IP access works — a TLS
# client on a bare IP sends no SNI.)
ASTERISM_DOMAIN=203.0.113.10

# "internal" -> self-signed local CA. An email -> Let's Encrypt (REQUIRES a real
# FQDN in ASTERISM_DOMAIN with a DNS A record pointing here and ports 80/443 open).
#   e.g. with a domain:  ASTERISM_DOMAIN=asterism.e4m.jp
#                        ASTERISM_TLS_EMAIL=you@e4m.jp
ASTERISM_TLS_EMAIL=internal

# ─── Whole-site gate (session-cookie login via the authgate service) ─────────
# Shared login password — entered once on the login page; a signed cookie then
# keeps you in from anywhere with no re-prompts. Use a strong value.
ASTERISM_GATE_PASSWORD=
# HMAC key that signs the session cookie. Long random secret WITHOUT '$':
#   openssl rand -hex 32
# Rotating it invalidates all sessions (everyone must log in again).
ASTERISM_GATE_SECRET=
# Optional: session lifetime in seconds (default 604800 = 7 days).
#ASTERISM_GATE_TTL=604800

# ─── API write/design token (api) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Gates write / design / raw-SPARQL routes (sent by the SPA as X-Asterism-Token).
# Unset -> those routes are DISABLED (503). Use a long random secret WITHOUT '$'
# (e.g. `openssl rand -hex 32`) so nothing downstream tries to interpolate it.
ASTERISM_API_TOKEN=

# ─── Ask CORS (demo-agent) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Same-origin via Caddy, so usually leave blank. If you call /demo from another
# origin, set it to that origin (e.g. https://asterism.e4m.jp).
ASTERISM_DEMO_CORS_ORIGINS=

# ─── Instance IRI base (api — identifier namespace for YOUR datasets) ────────
# Where THIS install mints the ontology/resource namespaces of newly designed
# datasets: `<base>/datasets/<slug>/ontology#` and `…/resource/`. IRIs are the
# permanent identity of your published facts — set a namespace you control and
# intend to keep (an org domain, or https://<user>.github.io/<repo>), NOT the
# deployment hostname if that may change. Unset -> https://asterism.invalid
# (RFC 2606: guaranteed to never resolve), which marks the data as not yet
# publicly homed — fine for local/trial use, replace it before publishing.
# Changing this NEVER rewrites existing datasets (IRI immutability); it only
# affects designs created afterwards. (example.org-style placeholder domains
# are rejected at design time, so don't paste one here.)
#ASTERISM_IRI_BASE=https://data.<your-domain>/asterism

# ─── Bundled example tools (OPTIONAL) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# By default Ask / the MCP surface serve ONLY the tools of datasets in YOUR
# workbench registry — what the catalog actually shows. Set to 1 to also serve
# the repo-bundled example datasets' tools (datasets/: starrydata,
# materials_project, papers). Meant for the standalone demo, not production.
#ASTERISM_BUNDLED_TOOLS=1

# ─── Operator LLM keys (OPTIONAL — "configure once" for this instance) ────────
# By default Asterism keeps provider keys OUT of the server: each user enters a
# key in Settings (kept in their browser, sent per request, never persisted).
# On a Private, login-gated instance you can instead hold the key ONCE here, and
# users won't need to enter one — propose / Ask / the model picker fall back to
# it when the browser sends none (a browser-supplied key still wins). Everyone
# behind the login shares this key (and its cost), which is the intent for a
# single-org box. Leave ALL of these UNSET on any multi-tenant / public instance.
#ASTERISM_LLM_KEY_ANTHROPIC=
#ASTERISM_LLM_KEY_OPENAI=
#ASTERISM_LLM_KEY_OPENAI_COMPATIBLE=
